Sentencas: Performance improvement of a thin film lanthanum strontium cobalt iron oxide (La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O1-delta, LSCF) cathode deposited by pulsed laser deposition (PLD) was achieved by utilizing a sputtered gold (Au) film as a current collecting layer.
Titulo: Performance Enhancement of Thin Film LSCF Cathodes by Gold Current Collecting Layer

Sentencas: To improve low in-plane electric conductivity of the porous LSCF film due to its columnar structure, fabrication of the well-connected and porous current collector is applied by sputtering.
Titulo: Performance Enhancement of Thin Film LSCF Cathodes by Gold Current Collecting Layer

Sentencas: The effects of the Au current collecting layer for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with the LSCF cathode are electrochemically characterized.
Titulo: Performance Enhancement of Thin Film LSCF Cathodes by Gold Current Collecting Layer

Sentencas: The cell without the current collecting layer shows 14 Omega.cm(2) of ohmic resistance, while the cell with the current collecting layer exhibits 5.5 Omega.cm(2) of ohmic resistance at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Performance Enhancement of Thin Film LSCF Cathodes by Gold Current Collecting Layer

Sentencas: In addition, the cell with the Au layer shows almost four times higher peak power density than the cell without the Au layer.
Titulo: Performance Enhancement of Thin Film LSCF Cathodes by Gold Current Collecting Layer

Sentencas: Therefore, the results suggest that the sputtered Au current collecting layer enables fabrication of porous LSCF cathode with enhanced electric conductivity and improves the performance of the fuel cell.
Titulo: Performance Enhancement of Thin Film LSCF Cathodes by Gold Current Collecting Layer
